data.title: Chubb Limited to recommend 33rd consecutive dividend increase at 2026 AGM, proposing $4.08 annual dividend.
data.description: Chubb Limited, a company traded on NYSE under the ticker symbol CB, revealed today in Zurich that its Board of Directors intends to propose at the 2026 Annual General Meeting a rise in the quarterly dividend for the 33rd straight year. The recommended increase would result in an annual dividend of $4.08.

data.title: Diana Shipping Inc. reports Q4 2025 net income of $3.1 million, declares $0.01 dividend per common share.
data.description: In Athens, Greece, on February 26, 2026, Diana Shipping Inc. (NYSE: DSX), a global shipping company specializing in dry bulk vessels' ownership and bareboat charter-in, announced its financial results for the fourth quarter of 2025. The company reported a net income of $3.1 million, with net income attributable to common stockholders totaling $1.7 million. This marks a decrease from the fourth quarter of 2024, where the company reported a net income of $9.7 million, with net income attributable to common stockholders at $8.3 million. Earnings per share for the fourth quarter of 2025 were $0.02 both basic and diluted, contrasting with $0.07 basic and $0.02 diluted during the same quarter of 2024.

data.title: Telekom Srbija gets landmark credit ratings from Fitch & Moody’s, the 1st in Western Balkans, paving the way for international growth.
data.description: Telekom Srbija Group, based in Belgrade, Serbia, made history by becoming the first company in the Western Balkans to receive international credit ratings from Fitch Ratings and Moody’s Investors Service. Fitch Ratings confirmed Telekom Srbija’s long-term issuer rating following the company's inaugural issuance of bonds on the global financial market. The rating agencies recognized the Group’s robust market presence and resilience. This achievement showcases the Group’s financial strength and credibility on a global scale.

data.title: PSEG raises common stock dividend by 6% to $2.68 per share, marking 15th consecutive increase and 119th year of paying shareholders.
data.description: Public Service Enterprise Group (NYSE: PEG) based in Newark, New Jersey, announced the 15th consecutive dividend increase, bringing the annual dividend rate up by approximately 6% to $2.68 per share. This marks the 119th year that the company has been paying dividends to shareholders. The Board of Directors declared a quarterly dividend of $0.67.
